title: Tioga, Deposit/Hancock roll in Class D quarterfinals
text:
Tioga, Deposit/Hancock roll in Class D quarterfinals 
By wbng sports October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 12:06 AM EDT 
Tioga Center, NY (WBNG Binghamton) Jesse Manuel scored on the first play from scrimmage and Tioga never trailed against Oxford as the Tigers earned a spot in the Section IV Class D semifinals with a 59-26 win. 
Tioga is chasing after its fifth straight Section IV crown. 
In other Class D playoff action, Deposit/Hancock trailed in the first quarter against seven-seed Groton, but it didn't last long. 
The Eagles responded by scoring 66 points in their quarterfinal win over the Indians. 
Deposit/Hancock moved on by the count of 66-12. 
Out west, Moravia went on the road and beat three-seed Elmira Notre Dame in the other Class D playoff game on Friday night. 
Jarod Lyon ran for for five touchdowns in the Blue Devils 39-13 win. 
Owego earns home playoff game Owego's Josh Goodrich scored right before halftime to give the Indians a 13-6 lead. That touchdown turned out to be enough as Owego held off Waverly, 13-12, to clinch a home playoff game next week. 
The Wolverines scored their final touchdown with a little over four minutes remaining, but didn't get the two-point conversion that would have given them the late lead. 
Instead, Owego walks away with the win and the Indians will host Waverly in next week's Section IV Class B semifinals.
